  <revision rev="2" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>639874d688c9ccea04acb49f08d1bf7a</srcmd5>
    <version>0.3.0</version>
    <time>1776009151</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>- Update to version 0.3.0:
  + Users are now fetched from AccountsService instead of /etc/passwd. This
    provides better integration with modern desktop environments
  + GTK cursor blinking can now be disabled via the cursor_blink option (forwarded request 1346123 from rrahl0)</comment>
    <requestid>1346124</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="3" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>9181f793dfc1eac389d48fe235368770</srcmd5>
    <version>0.4.0</version>
    <time>1780245005</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>- Update to version 0.4.0:
  + Config option to skip selecting user/session, with auto-login support and
    info message on skip. Passwordless users are excluded from auto-login
  + Added background image/webp/gif/video support via GStreamer
  + GTK4 pango markup is now supported in the clock widget format (the
    widget.clock.format configuration options)
  + The background_fit configuration option is now case-insensitive
  + greetd info messages are now displayed as notifications, just like greetd
    error messages
  + Session dropdown is not empty anymore on a fresh state file
  + Hid the border of the notification bar frame that shows up even when no
    notification is displayed (forwarded request 1356080 from rrahl0)</comment>
    <requestid>1356081</requestid>
  </revision>
</revisionlist>
